<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4 species; length 9-19 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Homothermon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homothermon" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Homothermon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes four uncommon species that are distributed in the Paulista center of endemism in Brazil and Argentina (Rio de Janeiro in the north to Santa Catarina, Rio Grande do Sul, and Misiones in the south) (
<bibRefCitation author="Mueller, P" journalOrPublisher="Junk, The Hague" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B253" refString="Mueller, P, 1973. The dispersal centres of terrestrial vertebrates in the Neotropical realm. Dr. W. Junk, The Hague" title="The dispersal centres of terrestrial vertebrates in the Neotropical realm. Dr. W." year="1973">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
1973
</bibRefCitation>
). Species in the genus are characterized by greatly enlarged metatibia in the male, claws on all legs simple (both male and female), male with a medial tubercle on the protarsal claw, pronotal basal bead incomplete anterior to the scutellum, elytral margin without a bead (=rounded), scutellum that is nearly twice as wide as long, clypeus semi-circular or subtrapezoidal, apex of mandibles bidentate, and parameres with a well-developed ventral plate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Classification and nomenclatural history of members of the genus has been confused. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="42 - 63" refId="B263" refString="Ohaus, F, 1898. Ruteliden der neuen Welt. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung 59: 42 - 63" title="Ruteliden der neuen Welt." volume="59" year="1898">Ohaus (1898)</bibRefCitation>
postulated that the genus was closely related to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Thyridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thyridium" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Thyridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Burmeister and placed it in the subtribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1856" genus="Anticheirina" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">Anticheirina</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1904.tb02746.x" author="Bates, F" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="249 - 276" refId="B7" refString="Bates, F, 1904. A revision of the sub-family Pelidnotinae of the coleopterous family Rutelidae, with descriptions of new genera and species. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1904: 249 - 276, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1904.tb02746.x" title="A revision of the sub-family Pelidnotinae of the coleopterous family Rutelidae, with descriptions of new genera and species." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1904.tb02746.x" volume="1904" year="1904">Bates (1904)</bibRefCitation>
omitted the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Homothermon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homothermon" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Homothermon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(even though it was described six years prior to his revision) and also overlooked 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Homothermon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homothermon praemorsus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praemorsus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Homothermon praemorsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Burmeister) (then classified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1855" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Strigidia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Strigidia praemorsus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="praemorsus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Strigidia praemorsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) even though he treated 
<taxonomicName family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Strigidia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Strigidia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Strigidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid genus. In the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Coleopterorum Catalogus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="42 - 63" refId="B263" refString="Ohaus, F, 1898. Ruteliden der neuen Welt. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung 59: 42 - 63" title="Ruteliden der neuen Welt." volume="59" year="1898">Ohaus 1898</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Coleopterorum Catalogus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 241" refId="B278" refString="Ohaus, F, 1918. Scarabaeidae: Euchirinae, Phaenomerinae, Rutelinae. Coleopterorum Catalogus 20: 1 - 241" title="Scarabaeidae: Euchirinae, Phaenomerinae, Rutelinae." volume="20" year="1918">1918</bibRefCitation>
), the genus was placed in the subtribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1844" class="Insecta" genus="Pelidnotina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pelidnotina</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Soula, M" journalOrPublisher="AECFT, Saintry" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B359" refString="Soula, M, 2008. Les Coleopteres du Nouveau Monde. Volume 2: Rutelini 2. Revision des Pelidnotina 2. Revision des genres: Parhoplognathus, Chipita n. gen., Heteropelidnota, Homothermon, Hoplopelidnota, Mesomerodon, Mecopelidnota, Patatra n. gen. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae, Rutelinae, Rutelini). Besoiro: Supplement au Bulletin de liaison de l'Association Entomologique pour la Connaissance de la Faune Tropicale. AECFT, Saintry" title="Les Coleopteres du Nouveau Monde. Volume 2: Rutelini 2. Revision des Pelidnotina 2. Revision des genres: Parhoplognathus, Chipita n. gen., Heteropelidnota, Homothermon, Hoplopelidnota, Mesomerodon, Mecopelidnota, Patatra n. gen. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae, Rutelinae, Rutelini). Besoiro: Supplement au Bulletin de liaison de l'Association Entomologique pour la Connaissance de la Faune Tropicale." year="2008">Soula (2008)</bibRefCitation>
commented that the genus 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“approaches”">&quot;approaches&quot;</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1819" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pelidnota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pelidnota" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pelidnota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the elytral margin that lacks a bead, it is possible that the genus may be allied with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jameson" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Plesiorutela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plesiorutela" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Plesiorutela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jameson (
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1819" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="tribe" tribe="Rutelini">Rutelini</taxonomicName>
). Future research should examine the relationships of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Homothermon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homothermon" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Homothermon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, placing it within a broad context of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1819" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="tribe" tribe="Rutelini">Rutelini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Homothermon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homothermon serrano" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrano">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Homothermon serrano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ohaus and 
<taxonomicName family="Scarabaeidae" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. bugre" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bugre">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. bugre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are apparently sympatric. Based on our examination of specimens (including type specimens), the two species differ only in color but are conspecific in all other respects. 
<bibRefCitation author="Soula, M" journalOrPublisher="AECFT, Saintry" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B359" refString="Soula, M, 2008. Les Coleopteres du Nouveau Monde. Volume 2: Rutelini 2. Revision des Pelidnotina 2. Revision des genres: Parhoplognathus, Chipita n. gen., Heteropelidnota, Homothermon, Hoplopelidnota, Mesomerodon, Mecopelidnota, Patatra n. gen. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae, Rutelinae, Rutelini). Besoiro: Supplement au Bulletin de liaison de l'Association Entomologique pour la Connaissance de la Faune Tropicale. AECFT, Saintry" title="Les Coleopteres du Nouveau Monde. Volume 2: Rutelini 2. Revision des Pelidnotina 2. Revision des genres: Parhoplognathus, Chipita n. gen., Heteropelidnota, Homothermon, Hoplopelidnota, Mesomerodon, Mecopelidnota, Patatra n. gen. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae, Rutelinae, Rutelini). Besoiro: Supplement au Bulletin de liaison de l'Association Entomologique pour la Connaissance de la Faune Tropicale." year="2008">Soula (2008)</bibRefCitation>
maintained 
<taxonomicName family="Scarabaeidae" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. serrano" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="serrano">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. serrano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName family="Scarabaeidae" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. bugre" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bugre">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. bugre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as separate species, and he stated that these are &quot;good examples of two populations where the aedeagus is very similar, however the populations represent two good species that are sympatric&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Soula, M" journalOrPublisher="AECFT, Saintry" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B359" refString="Soula, M, 2008. Les Coleopteres du Nouveau Monde. Volume 2: Rutelini 2. Revision des Pelidnotina 2. Revision des genres: Parhoplognathus, Chipita n. gen., Heteropelidnota, Homothermon, Hoplopelidnota, Mesomerodon, Mecopelidnota, Patatra n. gen. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae, Rutelinae, Rutelini). Besoiro: Supplement au Bulletin de liaison de l'Association Entomologique pour la Connaissance de la Faune Tropicale. AECFT, Saintry" title="Les Coleopteres du Nouveau Monde. Volume 2: Rutelini 2. Revision des Pelidnotina 2. Revision des genres: Parhoplognathus, Chipita n. gen., Heteropelidnota, Homothermon, Hoplopelidnota, Mesomerodon, Mecopelidnota, Patatra n. gen. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae, Rutelinae, Rutelini). Besoiro: Supplement au Bulletin de liaison de l'Association Entomologique pour la Connaissance de la Faune Tropicale." year="2008">Soula 2008</bibRefCitation>
: 31; translated from French). Lacking additional character evidence, we think that this is open to interpretation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Natural history for the genus is unknown. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Homothermon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homothermon serrano" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrano">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Homothermon serrano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the forested mountains near Theresopolis, Santa Catarina, Brazil (
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="42 - 63" refId="B263" refString="Ohaus, F, 1898. Ruteliden der neuen Welt. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung 59: 42 - 63" title="Ruteliden der neuen Welt." volume="59" year="1898">Ohaus 1898</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
